Ansible Integration with Kubernetes Cluster

Step 1: Start Kubernetes Cluster (Terminal)

Run:

minikube start --driver=docker

Verify cluster:

kubectl get nodes

Ensure status shows Ready

Step 2: Install Ansible (WSL Ubuntu / Linux Terminal)

Run:

sudo apt update
sudo apt install -y ansible

Verify:

ansible --version

Step 3: Install Kubernetes Collection for Ansible

Run:

ansible-galaxy collection install community.kubernetes

Step 4: Verify Kubernetes Connection

Run:

kubectl config view
kubectl get pods

Step 5: Create Test Playbook (test-k8s.yaml)

Create file:

test-k8s.yaml

Paste:

---

* name: Test Kubernetes Connection
  hosts: localhost
  connection: local
  gather_facts: no

  tasks:

  * name: List all pods in default namespace
    community.kubernetes.k8s_info:
    kind: Pod
    register: pod_list

  * debug:
    var: pod_list.resources

Step 6: Run Test Playbook

Run:

ansible-playbook test-k8s.yaml

Output shows list of pods

Step 7: Create Kubernetes Info Playbook (get-k8s-info.yaml)

Create file:

get-k8s-info.yaml

Paste:

---

* name: Gather Kubernetes Information
  hosts: localhost
  connection: local
  gather_facts: no

  tasks:

  * name: Get all namespaces
    community.kubernetes.k8s_info:
    kind: Namespace
    register: ns_info

  * debug:
    var: ns_info.resources

  * name: Get all nodes
    community.kubernetes.k8s_info:
    kind: Node
    register: node_info

  * debug:
    var: node_info.resources

Step 8: Run Info Playbook

Run:

ansible-playbook get-k8s-info.yaml

Output shows namespaces and nodes

Step 9: Cleanup

Delete namespace if created:

kubectl delete namespace ansible-lab

Stop cluster:

minikube stop

Delete cluster:

minikube delete

